Options available:
-----------------
**** - mandatory args

-t|--title) title of project


-s|--sampleFile) samplefile.csv
-i|--id) sanger id or sample id in the samplefile.csv
-e|--expType) rnaseq or chipseq
-d|--dataType) genecount,exoncount,tpms,fpkms
-c|--comments) user comments that can be added to metadata. Only alpha-numerics
-p|--procs) total processors (threads)
-m|--mem) total memory in MB
-f|--conf) configuration file
-q|--queue) queue type [normal,small,long,basement,yesterday]
-o|--organism) command specific option. read below
-g|--gtf) gtf file
-r|--paired) paired reads or not [0,1]
-v|--qval) pvalue or q value cut off [0-1]
-u|--inputFile) command specific option. Input files for certain commands
-y|--chrType) chromosome type [ucsc,ensembl]


**** Farm specific options
-x|--command) Command to be run. Used by farmsub.
-a|--array) [file of commands]. - Runs each line in the file 
-W|--walltime) [walltime, hh:mm] - Set a timed job
-T|--concurrent) [total number of concurrent array jobs] - if -a is specified you this to set number of jobs. 
-j|--waitForJob) [job_name] - Job name to wait.
-w|--wait) no args. Wait for the job to finish
-c|--comments) sample ids or names to be added
the bsub scripts will have title.comments.bsub file names

**** - program specific args. 
-0|--file0) optional file0 reserved for specific commands
-1|--file1) optional file0 reserved for specific commands
-2|--file2) optional file0 reserved for specific commands
-3|--file3) optional file0 reserved for specific commands
-4|--file4) optional file0 reserved for specific commands
-5|--file5) optional file0 reserved for specific commands

